 The nurses and general workers at Middelburg Provincial Hospital downed tools after an intruder tried to stab a matron. Read: Doctor assaulted The protest was prompted by a string of complaints the staff have raised with the hospital. Last year a nurse was assaulted, a few years ago two nurses were also stabbed and a doctor stabbed to death. Read: New hospital for Middelburg The workers are demanding the hospital management to intensify the security. One employee, who does not want to be named, said staff members feel unsafe. The demonstration started as employees are demanding to be addressed by provincial management and not local or district management. Read: Murdered man found outside hospital They feel as though the hospital management is “not taking their grievances seriously.” The protesters said they will not return to work until the province addresses their demands. Some staff members have reported for duty and ambulances are operating as usual. Read: Criminals invade hospital According to Middelburg Hospital board member Robert Xaba, the hospital had 12 security officers and management agreed to employ five more officers.  Vermeende huisrower eerste keer in hof Vroue in hospitaal na maermaak prosedure Elektrisiteitspyne die winter Vermeende plaasaanvaller verdwyn Strike on N11 Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za